fields.description:
Wherever a ScrollableView is used it has a black bar at the bottom. I created a new application and it has the same problem.


{code:xml}
<Alloy>
	<Window>
		<ScrollableView>
			<View title="Tab 1">
				<Label>I am page 1</Label>
			</View>
			<View title="Tab 2">
				<Label>I am page 2</Label>
			</View>
		</ScrollableView>
	</Window>
</Alloy>
{code}


{code:java}
"Window": {
	backgroundColor: "#fff"
}

"Label": {
	width: Ti.UI.SIZE,
	height: Ti.UI.SIZE,
	color: "#000",
	font: {
		fontSize: 20,
		fontFamily: 'Helvetica Neue'
	},
	textAlign: 'center'
} 
{code}

!Simulator Screen Shot Nov 10, 2015, 10.31.39 AM.png|thumbnail!

comments.body:
Hello , we have looked at the problem and believe this PR should fix it. While the showPagingControl property is set to false inside the scrollableView  you should no longer see the black footer. 

PR pending https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/pull/7436.
{code}
var win = Ti.UI.createWindow();

var view1 = Ti.UI.createView({ backgroundColor:'#123' });

var scrollableView = Ti.UI.createScrollableView({
  views:[view1],
  showPagingControl:false
});

win.add(scrollableView);
win.open();
{code}
